    • Method Detail

      • findNextMatch

        public void findNextMatch(FIFOWorkList<java.lang.Byte> buffer,
                          HuffmanCompressor huffman)
        Returns the terminal SuffixTrieNode representing the match. There are three cases: Case 1: We found normal a match. Then, this method will return a SuffixTrieNode that has a value. Case 2: We found a special match. Then, this method will return a SuffixTrieNode with NO VALUE. This SuffixTrieNode can be used to find the value by traversing all paths to find any leaf. Case 3: We found no match. Then, this method will return null.
        Parameters:
        buffer -
